{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":928,"text":"I decided when I was asked to do this"},{"time":2809,"text":"that what I really wanted to talk about\nwas my friend, Richard Feynman."},{"time":6531,"text":"I was one of the fortunate few\nthat really did get to know him"},{"time":10000,"text":"and enjoyed his presence."},{"time":12000,"text":"And I'm going to tell you\nabout the Richard Feynman that I knew."},{"time":15527,"text":"I'm sure there are people here\nwho could tell you"},{"time":17850,"text":"about the Richard Feynman they knew,"},{"time":19591,"text":"and it would probably be\na different Richard Feynman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22140,"text":"Richard Feynman was a very complex man."},{"time":24147,"text":"He was a man of many, many parts."},{"time":26464,"text":"He was, of course, foremost,\na very, very, very great scientist."},{"time":31798,"text":"He was an actor. You saw him act."},{"time":34000,"text":"I also had the good fortune\nto be in those lectures,"},{"time":37682,"text":"up in the balcony."},{"time":39536,"text":"They were fantastic."},{"time":41885,"text":"He was a philosopher."},{"time":43631,"text":"He was a drum player."},{"time":44825,"text":"He was a teacher par excellence."},{"time":48483,"text":"Richard Feynman was also a showman,"},{"time":51164,"text":"an enormous showman."},{"time":52751,"text":"He was brash, irreverent."},{"time":56186,"text":"He was full of macho,\na kind of macho one-upmanship."},{"time":61455,"text":"He loved intellectual battle."},{"time":65405,"text":"He had a gargantuan ego."},{"time":69157,"text":"But the man had, somehow,"},{"time":72657,"text":"a lot of room at the bottom."},{"time":75133,"text":"And what I mean by that\nis a lot of room, in my case --"},{"time":79887,"text":"I can't speak for anybody else,\nbut in my case --"},{"time":83000,"text":"a lot of room for another big ego."},{"time":86303,"text":"Well, not as big as his,"},{"time":87717,"text":"but fairly big."},{"time":90890,"text":"I always felt good with Dick Feynman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93136,"text":"It was always fun to be with him."},{"time":95586,"text":"He always made me feel smart."},{"time":97753,"text":"How can somebody like that\nmake you feel smart?"},{"time":99984,"text":"Somehow he did."},{"time":101174,"text":"He made me feel smart.\nHe made me feel he was smart."},{"time":103658,"text":"He made me feel we were both smart,"},{"time":105633,"text":"and the two of us could solve\nany problem whatever."},{"time":110083,"text":"And in fact, we did sometimes\ndo physics together."},{"time":113115,"text":"We never published a paper together,"},{"time":115184,"text":"but we did have a lot of fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118760,"text":"He loved to win,"},{"time":120679,"text":"win these little macho games\nwe would sometimes play."},{"time":123403,"text":"And he didn't only play them with me,\nbut with all sorts of people."},{"time":126691,"text":"He would almost always win."},{"time":128552,"text":"But when he didn't win, when he lost,"},{"time":131639,"text":"he would laugh and seem\nto have just as much fun"},{"time":134300,"text":"as if he had won."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136331,"text":"I remember once he told me a story"},{"time":138503,"text":"about a joke the students played on him."},{"time":140892,"text":"I think it was for his birthday --"},{"time":143453,"text":"they took him for lunch"},{"time":144894,"text":"to a sandwich place in Pasadena."},{"time":149536,"text":"It may still exist; I don't know."},{"time":151584,"text":"Celebrity sandwiches was their thing."},{"time":154190,"text":"You could get a Marilyn Monroe sandwich."},{"time":156554,"text":"You could get a Humphrey Bogart sandwich."},{"time":159373,"text":"The students went there in advance,"},{"time":161579,"text":"and arranged that they'd all order\nFeynman sandwiches."},{"time":165001,"text":"One after another, they came in\nand ordered Feynman sandwiches."},{"time":168012,"text":"Feynman loved this story."},{"time":169264,"text":"He told me this story,\nand he was really happy and laughing."},{"time":173322,"text":"When he finished the story, I said to him,"},{"time":176096,"text":"\"Dick, I wonder what\nwould be the difference"},{"time":178983,"text":"between a Feynman sandwich\nand a Susskind sandwich.\""},{"time":182491,"text":"And without skipping a beat at all,"},{"time":184530,"text":"he said, \"Well, they'd be about the same."},{"time":187796,"text":"The only difference is a Susskind\nsandwich would have a lot more ham.\""},{"time":191142,"text":"\"Ham\" as in bad actor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192851,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":194399,"text":"Well, I happened to have been\nvery quick that day,"},{"time":197833,"text":"and I said, \"Yeah,\nbut a lot less baloney.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":202978,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":204139,"text":"The truth of the matter"},{"time":207345,"text":"is that a Feynman sandwich\nhad a load of ham,"},{"time":211351,"text":"but absolutely no baloney."},{"time":215645,"text":"What Feynman hated worse\nthan anything else"},{"time":217942,"text":"was intellectual pretense --"},{"time":219968,"text":"phoniness,"},{"time":221221,"text":"false sophistication, jargon."},{"time":224950,"text":"I remember sometime during the mid-'80s,"},{"time":229242,"text":"Dick and I and Sidney Coleman\nwould meet a couple of times"},{"time":233400,"text":"up in San Francisco --\nat some very rich guy's house --"},{"time":236589,"text":"up in San Francisco for dinner."},{"time":238740,"text":"And the last time the rich guy invited us,"},{"time":241000,"text":"he also invited a couple of philosophers."},{"time":243160,"text":"These guys were philosophers of mind."},{"time":245712,"text":"Their specialty was the philosophy\nof consciousness."},{"time":249100,"text":"And they were full of all kinds of jargon."},{"time":251814,"text":"I'm trying to remember the words --"},{"time":254234,"text":"\"monism,\" \"dualism,\"\ncategories all over the place."},{"time":258148,"text":"I didn't know what those meant, neither\ndid Dick or Sydney, for that matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261746,"text":"And what did we talk about?"},{"time":263540,"text":"Well, what do you talk about\nwhen you talk about minds?"},{"time":266139,"text":"There's one obvious thing to talk about:"},{"time":268327,"text":"Can a machine become a mind?"},{"time":270578,"text":"Can you build a machine"},{"time":272331,"text":"that thinks like a human being\nthat is conscious?"},{"time":275841,"text":"We sat around and talked about this --\nwe of course never resolved it."},{"time":279195,"text":"But the trouble with the philosophers"},{"time":281000,"text":"is that they were philosophizing"},{"time":283000,"text":"when they should have been\nscience-ophizing."},{"time":285788,"text":"It's a scientific question, after all."},{"time":288152,"text":"And this was a very, very\ndangerous thing to do"},{"time":291083,"text":"around Dick Feynman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292536,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":295278,"text":"Feynman let them have it --\nboth barrels, right between the eyes."},{"time":298497,"text":"It was brutal; it was funny --\nooh, it was funny."},{"time":301592,"text":"But it was really brutal."},{"time":303329,"text":"He really popped their balloon."},{"time":306065,"text":"But the amazing thing was --\nFeynman had to leave a little early;"},{"time":309589,"text":"he wasn't feeling too well,\nso he left a little bit early."},{"time":312715,"text":"And Sidney and I were left there\nwith the two philosophers."},{"time":315633,"text":"And the amazing thing\nis these guys were flying."},{"time":318647,"text":"They were so happy."},{"time":320828,"text":"They had met the great man;"},{"time":323106,"text":"they had been instructed by the great man;"},{"time":325558,"text":"they had an enormous amount of fun"},{"time":327523,"text":"having their faces shoved in the mud ..."},{"time":330875,"text":"And it was something special."},{"time":333358,"text":"I realized there was something\njust extraordinary about Feynman,"},{"time":336771,"text":"even when he did what he did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343414,"text":"Dick -- he was my friend;\nI did call him Dick --"},{"time":346112,"text":"Dick and I had a little bit of a rapport."},{"time":348822,"text":"I think it may have been a special\nrapport that he and I had."},{"time":351720,"text":"We liked each other;\nwe liked the same kind of things."},{"time":354367,"text":"I also like the intellectual macho games."},{"time":358278,"text":"Sometimes I would win,\nmostly he would win,"},{"time":360382,"text":"but we both enjoyed them."},{"time":362000,"text":"And Dick became convinced at some point"},{"time":364414,"text":"that he and I had\nsome kind of similarity of personality."},{"time":369226,"text":"I don't think he was right."},{"time":370704,"text":"I think the only point\nof similarity between us"},{"time":372947,"text":"is we both like to talk about ourselves."},{"time":375169,"text":"But he was convinced of this."},{"time":378034,"text":"And the man was incredibly curious."},{"time":381112,"text":"And he wanted to understand\nwhat it was and why it was"},{"time":384810,"text":"that there was this funny connection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388374,"text":"And one day, we were walking."},{"time":390082,"text":"We were in France, in Les Houches."},{"time":391932,"text":"We were up in the mountains, 1976."},{"time":395580,"text":"And Feynman said to me, \"Leonardo ...\""},{"time":399862,"text":"The reason he called me \"Leonardo\"\nis because we were in Europe,"},{"time":402921,"text":"and he was practicing his French."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404596,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":406740,"text":"And he said, \"Leonardo,"},{"time":409987,"text":"were you closer to your mother\nor your father when you were a kid?\""},{"time":414000,"text":"I said, \"Well, my real hero was my father."},{"time":418057,"text":"He was a working man,"},{"time":420232,"text":"had a fifth-grade education."},{"time":422375,"text":"He was a master mechanic,\nand he taught me how to use tools."},{"time":425223,"text":"He taught me all sorts of things\nabout mechanical things."},{"time":429215,"text":"He even taught me the Pythagorean theorem."},{"time":431270,"text":"He didn't call it the hypotenuse,"},{"time":433247,"text":"he called it the shortcut distance.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":435855,"text":"And Feynman's eyes just opened up."},{"time":438656,"text":"He went off like a lightbulb."},{"time":441011,"text":"And he said that he had had"},{"time":443116,"text":"basically exactly the same\nrelationship with his father."},{"time":446870,"text":"In fact, he had been convinced at one time"},{"time":450314,"text":"that to be a good physicist,"},{"time":454149,"text":"it was very important to have had\nthat kind of relationship"},{"time":457506,"text":"with your father."},{"time":458686,"text":"I apologize for the sexist\nconversation here,"},{"time":461716,"text":"but this is the way it really happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463600,"text":"He said he had been absolutely\nconvinced that this was necessary,"},{"time":467421,"text":"a necessary part of the growing up\nof a young physicist."},{"time":471655,"text":"Being Dick, he, of course,\nwanted to check this."},{"time":474812,"text":"He wanted to go out and do an experiment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477112,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":478152,"text":"Well, he did."},{"time":479328,"text":"He went out and did an experiment."},{"time":481010,"text":"He asked all his friends\nthat he thought were good physicists,"},{"time":483949,"text":"\"Was it your mom or your pop\nthat influenced you?\""},{"time":486318,"text":"They were all men,"},{"time":488305,"text":"and to a man, every single\none of them said,"},{"time":490959,"text":"\"My mother.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":492207,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":495298,"text":"There went that theory,\ndown the trash can of history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499322,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":500450,"text":"But he was very excited\nthat he had finally met somebody"},{"time":503276,"text":"who had the same experience\nwith his father"},{"time":506896,"text":"as he had with his father."},{"time":508355,"text":"And for some time, he was convinced\nthis was the reason we got along so well."},{"time":512504,"text":"I don't know. Maybe. Who knows?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":514600,"text":"But let me tell you a little bit\nabout Feynman the physicist."},{"time":520622,"text":"Feynman's style --\nno, \"style\" is not the right word."},{"time":524600,"text":"\"Style\" makes you think\nof the bow tie he might have worn,"},{"time":527469,"text":"or the suit he was wearing."},{"time":528794,"text":"It's something much deeper than that,"},{"time":530737,"text":"but I can't think of another word for it."},{"time":532832,"text":"Feynman's scientific style\nwas always to look for the simplest,"},{"time":538298,"text":"most elementary solution\nto a problem that was possible."},{"time":542237,"text":"If it wasn't possible,\nyou had to use something fancier."},{"time":546469,"text":"No doubt, part of this\nwas his great joy and pleasure"},{"time":551065,"text":"in showing people that he could\nthink more simply than they could."},{"time":554837,"text":"But he also deeply believed,\nhe truly believed,"},{"time":558020,"text":"that if you couldn't explain\nsomething simply,"},{"time":560284,"text":"you didn't understand it."},{"time":563140,"text":"In the 1950s, people\nwere trying to figure out"},{"time":566417,"text":"how superfluid helium worked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569313,"text":"There was a theory."},{"time":570513,"text":"It was due to a Russian\nmathematical physicist."},{"time":572948,"text":"It was a complicated theory;"},{"time":574382,"text":"I'll tell you what it was soon enough."},{"time":576517,"text":"It was a terribly complicated theory,"},{"time":578389,"text":"full of very difficult\nintegrals and formulas"},{"time":581250,"text":"and mathematics and so forth."},{"time":583600,"text":"And it sort of worked,\nbut it didn't work very well."},{"time":586861,"text":"The only way it worked"},{"time":588227,"text":"is when the helium atoms\nwere very, very far apart."},{"time":591470,"text":"And unfortunately,"},{"time":594207,"text":"the helium atoms in liquid helium\nare right on top of each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597389,"text":"Feynman decided, as a sort\nof amateur helium physicist,"},{"time":600754,"text":"that he would try to figure it out."},{"time":603028,"text":"He had an idea, a very clear idea."},{"time":605456,"text":"He would try to figure out"},{"time":606874,"text":"what the quantum wave function\nof this huge number of atoms looked like."},{"time":611974,"text":"He would try to visualize it,"},{"time":613645,"text":"guided by a small number\nof simple principles."},{"time":616600,"text":"The small number of simple principles\nwere very, very simple."},{"time":619600,"text":"The first one was that when\nhelium atoms touch each other,"},{"time":623001,"text":"they repel."},{"time":624333,"text":"The implication of that is that\nthe wave function has to go to zero,"},{"time":627755,"text":"it has to vanish when the helium\natoms touch each other."},{"time":630864,"text":"The other fact\nis that in the ground state --"},{"time":633197,"text":"the lowest energy state\nof a quantum system --"},{"time":635958,"text":"the wave function is always very smooth;"},{"time":639253,"text":"it has the minimum number of wiggles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641372,"text":"So he sat down --"},{"time":642924,"text":"and I imagine he had nothing more"},{"time":645219,"text":"than a simple piece\nof paper and a pencil --"},{"time":647656,"text":"and he tried to write down,\nand did write down,"},{"time":649920,"text":"the simplest function\nthat he could think of,"},{"time":652239,"text":"which had the boundary conditions"},{"time":654240,"text":"that the wave function\nvanish when things touch"},{"time":656728,"text":"and is smooth in between."},{"time":659233,"text":"He wrote down a simple thing --\nso simple, in fact,"},{"time":661996,"text":"that I suspect a really smart\nhigh-school student"},{"time":665147,"text":"who didn't even have calculus"},{"time":666600,"text":"could understand what he wrote down."},{"time":669077,"text":"The thing was, that simple thing\nthat he wrote down"},{"time":672250,"text":"explained everything that was known\nat the time about liquid helium,"},{"time":675815,"text":"and then some."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677504,"text":"I've always wondered\nwhether the professionals --"},{"time":680505,"text":"the real professional helium physicists --"},{"time":682590,"text":"were just a little bit\nembarrassed by this."},{"time":685162,"text":"They had their super-powerful technique,"},{"time":687855,"text":"and they couldn't do as well."},{"time":689655,"text":"Incidentally, I'll tell you\nwhat that super-powerful technique was."},{"time":693806,"text":"It was the technique of Feynman diagrams."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696379,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":698260,"text":"He did it again in 1968."},{"time":701521,"text":"In 1968, in my own university --\nI wasn't there at the time --"},{"time":706531,"text":"they were exploring\nthe structure of the proton."},{"time":709497,"text":"The proton is obviously made\nof a whole bunch of little particles;"},{"time":713137,"text":"this was more or less known."},{"time":715522,"text":"And the way to analyze it was,\nof course, Feynman diagrams."},{"time":718882,"text":"That's what Feynman diagrams\nwere constructed for --"},{"time":721447,"text":"to understand particles."},{"time":723234,"text":"The experiments that were going on\nwere very simple:"},{"time":725870,"text":"you simply take the proton,"},{"time":727229,"text":"and you hit it really sharply\nwith an electron."},{"time":729863,"text":"This was the thing\nthe Feynman diagrams were for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732991,"text":"The only problem was that\nFeynman diagrams are complicated."},{"time":737078,"text":"They're difficult integrals."},{"time":738642,"text":"If you could do all of them,\nyou would have a very precise theory,"},{"time":741837,"text":"but you couldn't --\nthey were just too complicated."},{"time":745313,"text":"People were trying to do them."},{"time":746798,"text":"You could do a one-loop diagram.\nDon't worry about one loop."},{"time":749742,"text":"One loop, two loops --\nmaybe you could do a three-loop diagram,"},{"time":752771,"text":"but beyond that, you couldn't do anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754849,"text":"Feynman said, \"Forget all of that."},{"time":756517,"text":"Just think of the proton"},{"time":758012,"text":"as an assemblage, a swarm,\nof little particles.\""},{"time":762369,"text":"He called them \"partons.\""},{"time":764044,"text":"He said, \"Just think of it as a swarm\nof partons moving real fast.\""},{"time":769771,"text":"Because they're moving real fast,"},{"time":772996,"text":"relativity says the internal\nmotions go very slow."},{"time":777821,"text":"The electron hits it suddenly --"},{"time":779457,"text":"it's like taking a very sudden\nsnapshot of the proton."},{"time":784153,"text":"What do you see?"},{"time":785332,"text":"You see a frozen bunch of partons."},{"time":789390,"text":"They don't move,"},{"time":790596,"text":"and because they don't move\nduring the course of the experiment,"},{"time":793676,"text":"you don't have to worry\nabout how they're moving."},{"time":796009,"text":"You don't have to worry\nabout the forces between them."},{"time":798639,"text":"You just get to think of it\nas a population of frozen partons.\""},{"time":804314,"text":"This was the key to analyzing\nthese experiments."},{"time":807802,"text":"Extremely effective."},{"time":810987,"text":"Somebody said the word\n\"revolution\" is a bad word."},{"time":813513,"text":"I suppose it is,\nso I won't say \"revolution,\""},{"time":815678,"text":"but it certainly evolved very, very deeply\nour understanding of the proton,"},{"time":821204,"text":"and of particles beyond that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823370,"text":"Well, I had some more\nthat I was going to tell you"},{"time":826012,"text":"about my connection with Feynman,"},{"time":827693,"text":"what he was like,"},{"time":828891,"text":"but I see I have exactly half a minute."},{"time":831219,"text":"So I think I'll just finish up by saying:"},{"time":835170,"text":"I actually don't think\nFeynman would have liked this event."},{"time":837990,"text":"I think he would have said,\n\"I don't need this.\""},{"time":842882,"text":"But ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844056,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":845088,"text":"How should we honor Feynman?"},{"time":846470,"text":"How should we really honor Feynman?"},{"time":848176,"text":"I think the answer\nis we should honor Feynman"},{"time":851344,"text":"by getting as much baloney\nout of our own sandwiches"},{"time":855330,"text":"as we can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856941,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858116,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}